 would have been there even if <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> had not passed the bill,'' <PERSON> Grassley </PERSON> said. He called the foreclosure-expense test `` a very objective, bottom line decision that really means what <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> passed is n't costing the federal government anything.
