eturn several phone calls. The Pittses have been encouraged by <PERSON> Dan </PERSON> and <PERSON> Patricia </PERSON> <PERSON> Carter </PERSON> of <LOCATION> Spanish </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Fork </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Utah </LOCATION>, who recently won a highly publicized, seven-year custody fight with Navajo authorities over 10-year <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Halloway </PERSON> <PERSON> Carter </PERSON>. `` We spoke to them last night and they told us the only way we can win is to go public and tell our story to anyone who'll listen,'' Mrs. <PERSON> Pitts </PERSON> said `` I love my baby. I've waited a long time for her. The bond we have is very strong,'' she said. `` Sometimes she wo n't go to anybody else. She wakes up at night crying and does n't want to let go of us.''
