<BYLINE>With PM-Israel, Bjt
^By ROLAND PRINZ</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>VIENNA, Austria (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A <ORGANIZATION> U.N. </ORGANIZATION> health official who visited <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>'s occupied territories said today that <LOCATION> Palestinians </LOCATION> are suffering abdominal pain, miscarriages and muscular weakness from tear gas <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> is using against them. Dr. <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Hiddlestone </PERSON>, U.N. Relief and <ORGANIZATION> Works </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Agency </ORGANIZATION> director of health affairs, said in a telephone interview that he saw Palestinians experiencing symptoms `` which were not those usually associated with tear gas.'' But he added: `` I'm not actually accusing anybody of anything.'' The agency said the gas was being used improperly. The Israeli army denied the charge. Agency spokesman <PERSON> Ron </PERSON> <PERSON> Wilkinson </PERSON> reported several cases in which tear gas had been thrown into closed areas, houses, schools and a clinic in Israeli-held territory. `` It says right on the canisters that it must not be used in a confined area. So it -LRB- the gas -RRB- has particular toxic effects when it is thrown into a room,'' he said. `` One label says: ` For outdoor use only. Contents may cause severe injury if not used in accordance with this warning instruction.''' In the Israeli-occupied <LOCATION> Gaza </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Strip </LOCATION>, agency spokeswoman <PERSON> Christine </PERSON> <PERSON> Debaigh </PERSON> said a 70-year-old woman, <PERSON> Wadfah </PERSON> <PERSON> Farraj </PERSON> <PERSON> Allah </PERSON>, was dead on arrival at <LOCATION> Jabaliya </LOCATION>'s <ORGANIZATION> U.N. </ORGANIZATION> clinic on Wednesday after troops hurled a tear gas canister into her home. <LOCATION> Shifa </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hospital </LOCATION> officials said Mrs. <PERSON> Allah </PERSON> suffocated after inhaling the gas. An army spokesman denied the account and said that `` results of an autopsy carried out by the -LRB- government-run -RRB- <ORGANIZATION> Pathological </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Institute </ORGANIZATION> in <PERSON> Abu </PERSON> <PERSON> Kabir </PERSON> showed the woman died of natural causes.'' <ORGANIZATION> UNRWA </ORGANIZATION> is providing shelter, education and medical assistance to Palestinian refugees living in the <LOCATION> Middle </LOCATION> <LOCATION> East </LOCATION>. `` I am a physician and my worry is that people are having other symptoms than normal tear gas symptoms,'' <PERSON> Hiddlestone </PERSON> said. `` We need to know what's being used in the hope we can do more for these people because the abdominal pain is extremely severe of women who have been miscarrying and have had premature labor,'' he said. The doctor said he also met people suffering from `` great muscular weakness'' after exposure to gas used by the Israelis. He said those ailments occurred without eye, nose or throat irritation, `` so that even though you have tear gas which is in improper concentrations when it's put into closed spaces, the symptomatology of some people is not that which is normal as a result of tear gas.'' An army spokesman said: `` There is no truth to the report we are using a new type of toxic gas. The purpose of tear gas is to limit casualties and to cause as little damage as possible by avoiding physical confrontation with the rioters.'' He said tear gas could be lethal if inhaled by people already suffering from heart or other health problems, or if used in a small enclosed space. `` The army does not use tear gas in small enclosed spaces, at least not on purpose,'' said the spokesman, who spoke on condition of anonymity. The Boston-based Physicians for Human Rights has expressed concern that the Israelis may be misusing tear gas. The <ORGANIZATION> American-Arab </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Anti-Discrimination </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION>, a lobbying group, contends that more than 30 people have died in <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> and in the occupied <LOCATION> 