of former aides being accused and convicted of violating laws in connection with their service in his administration. <PERSON> Nofziger </PERSON>, a longtime <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> friend, said, `` Most of the people who have gotten in so-called trouble, it's been after they got out. ... I do n't know why anybody should blame the president for things that have happened to people after they left the White House.''
