<BYLINE>By ALLYN FISHER</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Palestinians staged a general strike across the occupied territories today to protest mass arrests of Arabs. Hospital officials said one Arab protester was killed and two wounded in clashes with <LOCATION> Israeli </LOCATION> soldiers. The strike, ordered by the PLO-affiliated underground leadership, was to support 4,800 Palestinians detained by <LOCATION> Israeli </LOCATION> troops since an Arab uprising was launched last December. Most of the 110,000 Palestinians with jobs in <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> did n't show up for work. Arab shopowners closed their doors in the cities of <LOCATION> Ramallah </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Nablus </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Bethlehem </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Hebron </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Jerusalem </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Gaza </LOCATION>. Since Dec. 8, 144 Palestinians and two Israelis have been killed in anti-occupation unrest in the <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bank </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Gaza </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Strip </LOCATION>, according to <ORGANIZATION> U.N. </ORGANIZATION> figures. Protests broke out today in two refugee camps in the <LOCATION> Gaza </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Strip </LOCATION> and two cities in the <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bank </LOCATION>, according to <PERSON> Arab </PERSON> media reports. <PERSON> Wael </PERSON> <PERSON> Hassan </PERSON> <PERSON> Asmar </PERSON>, 24, was shot in the heart and died at <LOCATION> Al </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Ittihad </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hospital </LOCATION> in the <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bank </LOCATION> city of <LOCATION> Nablus </LOCATION>, an emergency room official told The <ORGANIZATION> Associated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION>. The two wounded were identified as 12-year-old <PERSON> Mohammed </PERSON> <PERSON> Fuad </PERSON> <PERSON> Taha </PERSON>, who lost his right eye after being hit by a rubber bullet in <LOCATION> Tulkarem </LOCATION>, and <PERSON> Rebhi </PERSON> <PERSON> Shihada </PERSON> <PERSON> Rehan </PERSON>, 17, who was in critical conditon with a bullet wound in the stomach, said an official at <LOCATION> Rafidiyeh </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hospital </LOCATION> in <LOCATION> Nablus </LOCATION>. The army denied allegations that soldiers were using tear gas improperly against Palestinians or using a particularly toxic form of the gas. `` There is absolutely no truth to the report we are using a new type of toxic gas. The Israeli army does not use any toxic gases in dealing with Palestinian demonstrators,'' said an army spokesman, who in keeping with regulations, spoke on condition of anonymity. Dr. <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Hiddlestone </PERSON>, director of health affairs for the U.N. <ORGANIZATION> Relief </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Works </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Agency </ORGANIZATION>, said today that Palestinians are suffering abdominal pain, miscarriages and muscular weakness from tear gas. He said the symptoms are not usually associated with the gas. The director of <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>'s <ORGANIZATION> Government </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Office </ORGANIZATION>, <PERSON> Yoram </PERSON> <PERSON> Ettinger </PERSON>, said he plans to bar Palestinians from distributing press releases to foreign journalists in their mailboxes at the press office. `` Being committed to the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> they should n't expect <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>, whom the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> wants to destroy, to facilitate their dissemination of information,'' <PERSON> Ettinger </PERSON> told the English-language <ORGANIZATION> Jerusalem </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Post </ORGANIZATION> daily. <PERSON> Ettinger </PERSON>'s plans were protested by the <ORGANIZATION> Foreign </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION>. On Wednesday, soldiers arrested 70 Palestinians in a raid on the <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION>