<SECOND>AM-BRF--Rotten Eggs,0197</SECOND>
<HEAD>Paris Reeks Of Rotten Eggs</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PARIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 April in <LOCATION> Paris </LOCATION> is supposed to smell of blossoms and perfume, but for residents in some neighborhoods, it reeked of rotten eggs. Fire department officials said Thursday that for the second time in a week, they had received telephone calls inquiring into the source of the unpleasant odor that greeted them when they woke up Wednesday. Officials said they did not know where the smell was coming from, but that it posed no health hazard. The stench permeated three southern <LOCATION> Paris </LOCATION> neighborhoods and suburban areas. `` People start to worry when they leave their own neighborhoods and find the same awful smell in other parts of the city,'' said the official, who declined to be identified in keeping with departmental policy. The spokesman said the fire department had received about a dozen complaints. He said pollution levels were normal and that there was no evidence a toxic substance had leaked over the city. `` No industrial facilities warned of spills,'' he said. The smells could not be identified, he said, because `` smells are very subjective and different people smelled different things.''
