one of the other two men who escaped with <PERSON> Stacy </PERSON>, ran away after deputies pulled him over <PERSON> Mollohan </PERSON>, said <LOCATION> Marshall </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION> sheriff's dispatcher <PERSON> Lynell </PERSON> <PERSON> Kearans </PERSON>, gave deputies his correct last name, Social Security number and date of birth, but added a fictitious first name. He fled when the deputy radioed headquarters for confirmation of the information, she said. `` He ran down over the hill, and we're in the process of a manhunt right now,'' Ms. <PERSON> Kearans </PERSON> said. Authorities found a shotgun and shells in the car, as well as .22 - caliber ammunition with no corresponding weapon, and said they assume <PERSON> Mollohan </PERSON> is <PERSON> Mollohan </PERSON> was convicted of robbing and then killing a grocer in 1973. At the time, <PERSON> Mollohan </PERSON> had escaped from a <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION> prison and also was wanted in <LOCATION> Georgia </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> North </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Carolina </LOCATION> on armed robbery charges. The third escapee is <PERSON> David </PERSON> <PERSON> Williams </PERSON>, 28. He was convicted of felony murder, arson and robbery in the December 1980 slaying of a Marytown, <LOCATION> W. </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Va. </LOCATION>, resident who was found bludgeoned in the rubble of his burned home All three men were serving life terms. Numerous sightings of the escapees have been reported since the three used stolen bolt cutters to escape from the prison at <LOCATION> Moundsville </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> W. </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Va </LOCATION>
