lying with the whaling moratorium, <PERSON> Evans </PERSON> said. Under a 1967 law, the president may order an embargo of the fishery products of any country conducting a fishing operation that diminishes the effectiveness of an international fishery conservation program. <ORGANIZATION> Verity </ORGANIZATION> said he hopes the Soviet cessation of commercial whaling will allow for an expansion of fishing cooperation provided for in a new agreement signed Feb. 21.
