<HEAD>Filmmakers: Movies Doesn't Glorify Gang Violence</HEAD>
<HEAD>LaserPhoto upcoming</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By SUE MANNING</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The violent, realistic gang drama `` Colors'' opens Friday at 425 theaters across the country amid a debate between its critics and its makers over whether the film will inspire more youth violence. A spokesman for one group of law enforcement officers says the movie will `` leave dead bodies from one end of this town to the other,'' but the filmmakers say the film is a statement of conscience and will save lives. `` This is not the right time to release a movie like this,'' said <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION> City Councilman <PERSON> Nate </PERSON> <PERSON> Holden </PERSON>. Since April 4, there have been 89 gang-related deaths in <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION> city and county; last year, there were 387 gang-related deaths in the area. `` If there is anything this picture does not do _ it does not glorify gangs or gang violence,'' said <PERSON> Charles </PERSON> <PERSON> O. </PERSON> <PERSON> Glenn </PERSON>, executive vice president for the distributor, New York-based <ORGANIZATION> Orion </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Pictures </ORGANIZATION>. In <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> on Thursday, six members of the <ORGANIZATION> Guardian </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Angels </ORGANIZATION>, a community anti-crime group, were arrested during a protest outside Orion headquarters. The group planned a protest later Thursday in <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION>. The movie, starring <PERSON> Sean </PERSON> <PERSON> Penn </PERSON> and <PERSON> Rubert </PERSON> <PERSON> Duvall </PERSON> as gang-fighting <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION> policemen, was directed by <PERSON> Dennis </PERSON> <PERSON> Hopper </PERSON> and used active area gang members as extras and advisers. The film portrays the world of the Crips and the Bloods, rival gangs, who use the colors blue and red, respectively, to distinguish themselves. It was made with the `` technical advice, assistance and cooperation of the <ORGANIZATION> LAPD </ORGANIZATION>, its anti-gang CRASH unit, the Sheriff's <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Los </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Angeles </ORGANIZATION> and the <ORGANIZATION> Los </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Angeles </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> County </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Probation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION>,'' <PERSON> Glenn </PERSON> said But it has drawn strong criticism from some police, city officials, the <ORGANIZATION> NAACP </ORGANIZATION>, community leaders and the Guardian Angels. <PERSON> Wes </PERSON> <PERSON> McBride </PERSON>, president of the <ORGANIZATION> California </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Gang </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Investigators </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION>, believes `` Colors'' will `` leave dead bodies from one end of this town to the other.'' `` A release of this film may tip the scale in such a way that will only result in more loss of young lives,'' said <PERSON> Willis </PERSON> <PERSON> Edwards </PERSON>, president of the Beverly Hills-Hollywood <ORGANIZATION> NAACP </ORGANIZATION> chapter. `` I think the people who are making those predictions are whipping up the probability and the possibility,'' of violence, <PERSON> Hopper </PERSON> said. `` The people who are saying blood is going to flow in the streets are asking for blood to flow in the streets. I think it's very irresponsible behavior.'' About 70 theaters in the <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION> area alone plan to show `` Colors.'' Many critics called on theaters to cancel the movie. The downtown Laemmle Grand did just that. `` The staff at the theater were in a panic because the home turf of one of the gangs in the movie is just a couple of miles from downtown,'' said <PERSON> Bob </PERSON> <PERSON> Laemmle </PERSON>, theater chain co-owner. But <PERSON> Joel </PERSON> <PERSON> Maliniak </PERSON>, spokesman for the <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Civil </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Liberties </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Union </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Southern </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> California </ORGANIZATION>, said: `` Officials should be finding solutions to the gang problem rather than prohibiting something from being shown.'' District Attorney <PERSON> Ira </PERSON> <PERSON> Reiner </PERSON> said he believes the movie will galvanize support for the county's war on gangs. At a celebrity showing Wednesday night, which drew <PERSON> Cher </PERSON>, <PERSON> Marlee </PERSON> <PERSON> Matlin </PERSON>, <PERSON> Richard </PERSON> <PERSON> Dean </PERSON> <PERSON> Anderson </PERSON>, <PERSON> Bono </PERSON> <PERSON> Hewson </PERSON> and <PERSON> Emilio </PERSON> <PERSON> Estevez </PERSON>, 10 members of the <ORGANIZATION> Guardian </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Angels </ORGANIZATION> marched and chanted `` Do n't Show ` Colors.''' `` There is nothing in this film that glorifies being in a gang,'' said <PERSON> Hopper </PERSON>, who also attended the VIP showing. Five Guardian Angels were arrested Tuesday when they tried to force their way into <ORGANIZATION> Orion </ORGANIZATION>'s <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION> offices. The Angels, including group founder <PERSON> Curtis </PERSON> <PERSON> Sliwa </PERSON> who has called the movie `` racist and irresponsible,'' were arrested for investigation of battery after allegedly pushing and tackling security guards. `` We feel that ` Colors' is an honest and socially responsible portrayal of a problem that obviously exists in <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION> and in the streets of every other American city,'' <PERSON> Glenn </PERSON> said. He called `` Colors'' a `` significant work by filmmakers of substance and integrity,'' and likened it to statement movies made in the past, including `` Gentleman's Agreement'' about anti-Semitism, `` I Am a Fugitive from A Chain Gang'' about legal injustice, `` Platoon'' about the futility of combat and `` On the Waterfront'' about waterfront gangs.
