N> Kay </PERSON> wrote. Responded <PERSON> Obeidat </PERSON>: `` I reject the occupation because it stole my land, my freedom and my school.'' `` I do n't think when I ask for my freedom and my state that I am commiting a violent act or being an extremist. If you, <PERSON> Lior </PERSON>, were a Palestinian boy I think you probably would have fought the occupation as the Palestinian kids are fighting.'' `` We are not the reason for your suffering, <PERSON> Lior </PERSON>. This is not our fault. But you are the reason of our suffering. This is your fault.'' <PERSON> Obeidat </PERSON> said Israelis who returned to their ancient homeland had not been considerate of the Palestinians living on the same land. `` When you came back to live beside us what is the gift which you brought for me, an airplane, a tank, a gun and tear gas bombs? Is that a peaceful offering from a peaceful child, <PERSON> Lior </PERSON>? `` I am asking the Jews ... to quit using physical force, weapons and tear gas which kills love and peace and innocents like me and like you.'' `` This is the only way to build the bridges for peace and love between our nations and to build a peaceful state.''
