d and an adult as 21 or over. Personality development and family environment also play a role in determining what category is applicable, the newspaper <ORGANIZATION> Frankfurt </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Allgemeine </ORGANIZATION> said Thursday. Files in the Hesse prosecutor's office give <PERSON> Hamadi </PERSON>'s birth date as June 13, 1964, which would have made him 21 the day the hijacking began on June 14, 1985. Asked how long the juvenile court would study the case before setting a trial date, <PERSON> Kehren </PERSON> said: `` My guess would be in a month, maybe a little longer. But to say six months as some have been asking about is in my opinion way off the mark.'' The <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> asked <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Germany </LOCATION> to extradite <PERSON> Hamadi </PERSON> on murder and hijacking charges, but the West Germans turned down the request and said he would be tried here. <PERSON> Mohammed </PERSON> <PERSON> Hamadi </PERSON>'s brother <PERSON> Abbas </PERSON> is on trial in <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Germany </LOCATION> on charges of kidnapping two West Germans in <LOCATION> Lebanon </LOCATION> to use as ransom for the release of his brother. One of the hostages has been freed. Both Hamadis were living in <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Germany </LOCATION> when they were arrested two weeks apart at the <LOCATION> Frankfurt </LOCATION> airport in January 1987 on charges of possessing explosives.
