<HEAD>Unisys Net Income Up 35 Percent in First Quarter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BLUE BELL, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Computer manufacturer <ORGANIZATION> Unisys </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> reported a 35 percent increase in net earnings for the first quarter, citing continued savings from the summer 1986 merger of <PERSON> Sperry </PERSON> and <LOCATION> Burroughs </LOCATION>. Net income was $ 149.3 million, or 72 cents per fully diluted common share, for the three months ended March 31. For the same period a year ago, <ORGANIZATION> Unisys </ORGANIZATION> net income was $ 110.2 million, or 57 cents per fully diluted common share, adjusted for a July 1987 three-for-one stock split. Revenue fell 2.1 percent to $ 2.37 billion from $ 2.42 billion a year ago, when heavy end-of-the-year selling related to the old Sperry fiscal calendar raised revenues above typical first-quarter levels, the company reported. `` Our conservative business plan for 1988 and the cost advantages that continue to accrue to us from the merger put us in a strong position to achieve our plan in a modest business environment,'' said <ORGANIZATION> Unisys </ORGANIZATION> President <PERSON> W. </PERSON> <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Blumenthal </PERSON>. <ORGANIZATION> Unisys </ORGANIZATION>, created in 1986 from <ORGANIZATION> Burroughs </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>'s $ 4.8 billion purchase of <ORGANIZATION> Sperry </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>, is the world's third-largest computer company after <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Business </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Machines </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Digital </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Equipment </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> `` We are pleased with results for the quarter as earnings exceeded expectations and our continued progress faster than planned augurs well for achieving our aggressive five-year growth goals,'' <PERSON> Blumenthal </PERSON> said. `` Business in the quarter was basically on target, with order and revenue trends similar to what we experienced in 1987, when international business was generally stronger than in the <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Unisys </ORGANIZATION> operations continue to benefit from the fundamental structural changes made in 1986 and 1987,'' he said. <ORGANIZATION> Unisys </ORGANIZATION> reports its earnings per share on a fully diluted basis _ that is, based on the number of shares that would exist if all stock options were exercised and all convertible preferred shares were converted into common stock. Earnings per primary common share were up to 77 cents from 57 cents a year earlier.
